<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                    <head>No. 185.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Welsh</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 21,
                            1878</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Evarts</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary, Washington:</hi></p>
                    <p>Salisbury officially informs me the cabinet will recommend Queen to remit
                        remainder of the sentence of Condon and Melody.</p>
                    <p>Queen’s action not yet communicated.</p>
                    <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                    <closer><signed>WELSH,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Minister</hi>.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>